<Worksheet ss:Name="Overview"><Table><Column ss:Width="200"/><Column ss:Width="360"/><Column ss:Width="240"/><Row><Cell ss:StyleID="title" ss:MergeAcross="2"><Data ss:Type="String">Eco Assignment 2 Workbook</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell ss:StyleID="note" ss:MergeAcross="2"><Data ss:Type="String">Excel-compatible workbook built from the visible assignment statement. Standard assumptions were added where the screenshot did not fully show the product-cost table.</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell ss:StyleID="subtitle" ss:MergeAcross="2"><Data ss:Type="String">How to use</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell ss:StyleID="section"><Data ss:Type="String">Capital investment Goal Seek</Data></Cell><Cell ss:MergeAcross="1"><Data ss:Type="String">On sheet Capital Investment, set residual cell B35 to 0 by changing B18 (fixed-capital-investment guess).</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell ss:StyleID="section"><Data ss:Type="String">Product cost Goal Seek</Data></Cell><Cell ss:MergeAcross="1"><Data ss:Type="String">On sheet Product Cost, set profit residual cell B39 to 0 by changing B6 (selling price per unit).</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell ss:StyleID="section"><Data ss:Type="String">Yellow cells</Data></Cell><Cell ss:MergeAcross="1"><Data ss:Type="String">Editable assumptions / decision variables.</Data></Cell></Row><Row><Cell ss:StyleID="section"><Data ss:Type="String">Blue / gray cells</Data></Cell><Cell ss:MergeAcross="1"><Data ss:Type="String">Formula cells; do not type over them unless you want to change the model.</Data></Cell></Row></Table></Worksheet>
